Heerema Marine Contractors
HR Assistant Service Desk
Are you customer oriented and keen on having a perfect administration? Then you might be perfect for the role of HR Assistant Service Desk.
Human Resources
Leiden
Starter
A unique maritime adventure
At Heerema Marine Contractors we make the impossible, possible. With the biggest semi-submersible crane vessels (SSCV) of the world we transport, install and decommission wind farms and offshore platforms on sea. As a colleague both in the office or offshore, you are part of this unique maritime adventure.
Your role in the story
We are looking for an teammate to strengthen our HR Assistants team at the Service Desk. The HR Service Desk team consists of 5 teammates and is the first point of contact for all HR related matters. As a HR Assistant, you will assist our employees with all kind of HR related questions. Conducting a precise and efficient administration is the core business of the HR Assistant, this includes providing excellent service to our employees.
Your daily activities
Answering questions from employees face to face, by phone or by e-mail;
Preparing and handing HR correspondence (for example; employment contracts, employers statements, promotion letters, etc);
Checking correspondence and transactions of your Service Desk colleagues to guarantee the best quality;
Processing of personnel changes in our current SAP HR system in order to prepare the monthly payroll;
You will also have a role in the preparation and implementation to a new HR system with a focus on employee self-service.


Is this the job for you?
The ideal profile of our new HR Assistant – Service Desk:
Professional working experience as a HR Assistant is preferred
Up to date knowledge of the Dutch labor law
Experienced user of an employee self-service system is considered an advantage;
Used to working with sensitive information and working knowledge of GDPR;
Process minded, accurate, quality- and result orientated;
Fluent in Dutch and English, both written and spoken;
Available for 32 – 40 hours per week.
Here is what it takes to be a real Heerema colleague
Learning mindset, which means being open to feedback, curious, and eager to learn;
Personal leadership which means you are an entrepreneur at heart, have the mindset of a founder and take control of your own work and development.

Working at Heerema Marine Contractors
Making the impossible possible offshore, this is what drives us at Heerema! To execute our offshore projects we must innovate, engineer and develop to find solutions for our clients’ challenges. We are passionate about sustainability and are guided by our Sustainability Roadmap to reduce our impact on the planet. Working with Heerema means working in an international, informal, and friendly environment where you will meet likeminded and passionate colleagues.
Here's why people love working with us
Excellent secondary labor conditions, such as a bonus payment, a first-class pension scheme and various insurance plans;
Holiday; 30 working days;
Ample opportunities for personal and professional development;
Free use of Heerema's in-house fitness facility;
Opportunities to develop your initiatives within a team;
An informal working environment with international colleagues;
A centrally located office with a good accessibility and parking.
Is this your dream job? Put in your application now!
We are looking forward to hearing from you. We are interested in your CV, but we mainly want to find out more about your ambitions, your personality, and what is your motivation to succeed. So be sure to include a brief cover letter explaining why you are the perfect fit for this position.
So hit the button, apply, and make the impossible possible with Heerema. We’d love to meet you!
The application process
The application process will consist of an online assessment, two interviews and contract negotiations. At the end of the process, we will cordially welcome you aboard.

Heerema Marine Contractors
Jr. Business Controller
Do you have in depth financial knowledge needed for managing the operating financials of Heerema's Fleet and Equipment? Join our team in Leiden as Jr. Business Controller.
Control
Leiden
Starter
A unique maritime adventure
At Heerema Marine Contractors, we do something new every day. We operate the world’s largest crane vessels and with them we transport, install and remove offshore structures for the offshore energy markets. Our projects range from installing wind turbines, removing retired offshore oil and gas platforms, and installing platforms up to 50,000 metric tons. By joining us, you will play an important part in our unique maritime adventure.
Your role in the story
As Business Controller, you are one of the key figures within the Operations and Equipment department and you perform internal financial analysis and monitor budget and forecast. You prepare yearly forecasts, you take ownership for correct cost allocation to projects and you perform analysis on all operating OPEX and CAPEX (Operations, Crewing, Departmental, Maintenance, Replacements). You are responsible for monthly financial management information, in which you need to gather, combine and interpret information from different disciplines.
Who will you work with?
Your team will consist of Jeroen, Thijs and many others. You will work closely with the Operations & Equipment department and it will be your job to:
Complete the monthly financial close process including analytical review of the variances;
Prepare yearly budgets and related financial reporting and provide management with periodic accurate information to reach their targets as set in yearly budgets;
Review, update and develop forecasting methods for various cost types to improve and maintain high quality forecasts. Ensuring jointly with Budget Holders, optimum administration and insight in costs per cost type and assets;
Provide ad hoc reporting as required by the Operations & Equipment department / Lead Asset Control;
Prepare the annual close-out and related statutory and consolidated balance statements for Fixed Assets and Inventory;
Is this the job for you?
A Bachelor’s degree preferably in Finance or equivalent;
A minimum of 0-2 years relevant working in financial control;
Thorough knowledge of Microsoft Suite in particular Excel, SAP and Sharepoint;
Excellent communication skills, fluent in English both written and spoken.
Here is what it takes to be a real Heerema colleague
Learning mindset, which means being open to feedback, curious, and eager to learn;
Personal leadership which means you are an entrepreneur at heart, have the mindset of a founder and take control of your own work and development.
Working at Heerema Marine Contractors
Making the impossible possible offshore, this is what drives us at Heerema! To execute our offshore projects we must innovate, engineer and develop to find solutions for our clients’ challenges. We are passionate about sustainability and are guided by our Sustainability Roadmap to reduce our impact on the planet. Working with Heerema means working in an international, informal, and friendly environment where you will meet likeminded and passionate colleagues.
Here's why people love working with us
Working on challenging projects.
Extensive onboarding process and opportunities to develop.
A development program to allow your talents to flourish.
Fun Friday-afternoon get together with colleagues;
Excellent perks and benefits, including a personal performance bonus, travel allowance, and contributions to your pension and insurance;
Free exercise facilities;
A social safety net with committed colleagues around you;
Plenty of digital and real-world activities to get to know colleagues outside your team;
30 days off to fully recharge.
A modern and easily accessible office in Leiden.
Is this your dream job? Put in your application now!
We are looking forward to hearing from you. We are interested in your CV, but we mainly want to find out more about your ambitions, your personality, and what is your motivation to succeed. So be sure to include a brief cover letter explaining why you are the perfect fit for this position.
So hit the button, apply and make the impossible possible with Heerema. We’d love to meet you!
The application process
The application process will consist of an online assessment, two interviews and contract negotiations. At the end of the process, we will cordially welcome you aboard.

WE ARE SHELL RECHARGE SOLUTIONS
We are Europe’s largest electric charging partner. We are on a mission to enable everybody to drive as many kilometres as possible powered by clean energy. We do that by offering large scale smart charging solutions to the masses. We contribute to a low-carbon world by making EV charging easy, accessible and smart, with the best expertise, highest quality & service.


WHAT YOU’LL BE IN CHARGE OF

Your core accountabilities are...

Prepare monthly and quarterly performance appraisal reports to compare forecasted and actual results;
Discuss with Regional Managers and other budget owners, and define and follow-up on opportunities and corrective actions;
Prepare and host monthly working capital review which include maintaining and improving the working capital model for cash flow forecast;
Participate in the planning and appraisal cycles for SRS EU (strategic planning, budget, forecasts), working closely with the different business owners and budget holders, including the improvement and maintenance of complex forecasting models;
Analysing financial and non-financial insights including monthly update of the corporate and regional scorecard (KPI dashboard);
Work on continuous improvement of existing reporting/forecasting processes to adapt to the fast changing environment with increasing digital capability and changing portfolio/ organisation;
Together with the financial control team, improve the accuracy and reliability of our financial administration.

Success will be when you...
Are passionate to make the right information visible, translating data into insights and bringing numbers to life. So you are making sure that the right information is being brought forward to the business to have them make informed decisions in order to build a financially healthy business;
Continuously improve and develop streamlining the different processes with focus on digitalisation - with evolving needs from the business - generating high-quality and timely forecasts and reports;
Build strong relationships with different stakeholders within the business.
THE PERSON WE'RE LOOKING FOR WILL...
Have...

A Bachelor or Master degree in Business Administration, Finance, or equivalent;
4+ years of experience in a Controlling or Business Control/Analyst position;
Excellent knowledge and skills of data analysis and forecasting models, and a solid understanding of financial statistics and accounting principles.

Be skilled at…

Communicating clearly, and ability to translate insights into actionable agenda that is well understood by business colleagues in non-financial terms;
Problem solving with strong analytical skills enabling a quick understanding of data and translating these into relevant insights. Ability to cut through complexity and articulate clear and concise messages;
Excellent knowledge and skills of data analysis and forecasting models, and a solid understanding of financial statistics and accounting principles;
Collaborating effectively and professionally across the organisation with ability to influence others to deliver without direct authority.

Be...

Expert in Microsoft Excel, experience with Software packages Microsoft Dynamics NAV, LucaNet and DOMO, (or any other BI Tooling);
Fluent English language; additional languages like Dutch, German, French or others are a plus;
Curious, independent and can deal with high level of ambiguity;
Teamplayer that collaborate within and outside Finance and is credible with different levels of stakeholders;
A quick learning with a continuous improvement mindset;
Self-starter able to work proactively and independently as well as in a matrix organisation or project team;
Comfortable with change and working in an agile environment.
BECOME PART OF THE CHANGE
Working at Shell Recharge Solutions means working in a fun, fast-growing international company with big ambitions.

By joining us, you will:

Contribute to a more sustainable future
Become an expert in e-mobility
Work in an open and transparent culture with colleagues from all over the world
Receive a competitive salary that fits your experience + bonus
Enjoy daily healthy lunches, prepared by our masterchefs
Develop your skills and expertise through several trainings. Besides this, you will receive a personal training budget and set your annual goals with your personal development plan
Enjoy our fun weekly get-togethers (drinks), our annual winter and summer outing, Shell Recharge Solutions running team on the Dam tot Damloop, or any other event initiated by colleagues!

WE ARE SHELL RECHARGE SOLUTIONS

We're on a mission to enable cleaner transportation for everyone, driving the way towards a lower-carbon future. We do this by designing and building solutions for charging electric vehicles at home, at work, and on-the-go.
With some of the most passionate and experienced minds on our side, we aim to make charging easy and accessible. Our award-winning services include charge points, a mobile app, and a charge card, providing access to 480,000 charge points in over 33 countries.

WHAT YOU’LL BE IN CHARGE OF

At this position you will take the lead in the financial aspects of the Expansion Activities of the Company. Work closely with external tax advisor in the countries where the company wishes to expand, define the needs and coordinate with external and internal stakeholders (IT, Expansion team, Finance Control, Tax advisors, Banks, etc.) the requirements to start operations in the designated country. Once a new country is operating, you will be responsible for the administration of the entity and ensure compliance. You will work closely with the other Financial Controllers to ensure a timely, complete and accurate month end closing of all our European entities. You will be responsible for a proper accounting of our intercompany operation, intercompany reconciliation and transfer pricing. You will support the team with monthly reconciliations, reporting, and analyses. In addition you will assist with the different audits, the consolidated annual accounts and any other team-wide project. You will help improve the financial administration by signalling tasks and processes open to improvements with a focus on scalability. You’ll report directly to the Finance Control Team Leader.
Your core accountabilities are...

Monitor all accounting operations for the assigned entities;
Lead the financial & compliance aspects of new countries to be incorporated;
Be the first point of contact within the Finance team for the Expansion department;
Be responsible for the Intercompany transactions, reconciliation and transfer pricing;
Take part of the month-end process for your assigned entities and publish timely monthly financial figures;
Prepare year-end close process and the required additional documentation;
Prepare tax filings and help comply with local reporting requirements;
Take care of country specific topics for your assigned entities (e.g. subsidies or Intrastat);
Assist with the preparation for local audits;
Support the team with additional reporting requirements;
Support the team with the consolidated audit and annual accounts;
Develop a high level understanding of the business;
Manage the relation with internal and external stakeholders;
Investigate efficiency and automation opportunities,
Implement improvements accordingly.

Success will be when you...

Are a team player, flexible and perseverant;
Have strong interpersonal and communication skills;
Are eager to learn and improve.
THE PERSON WE'RE LOOKING FOR WILL...
Have...

A Master’s degree in Accounting, Business Administration, Finance, or equivalent;
More than 5 years of experience in a Finance, Controlling or Accounting position;
A solid understanding of financial processes and accounting principles.
Be skilled at...

Working in Excel and other MS Office packages at advanced level;
Academic level (WVO niveau) Working / thinking;
Internal and external communication, written and spoken;
Reporting and analysis.

Be...

Fluent in English, both written and spoken. Dutch is a great plus;
A strong team player and have a problem solving attitude;
Independent, Self-steering, flexible and perseverant.
Have knowledge of...

Microsoft Dynamics NAV, SalesForce and LucaNet would be a plus;
Have knowledge of BI is a strong plus;
Have experience in transfer pricing is a strong plus;
Experience with Telecom, automotive, mobility and/or utility is a strong plus.
WHAT IS IN IT FOR YOU?

Working at Shell Recharge Solutions means working in a fun, fast-growing international company with big ambitions.

By joining us, you will:

Contribute to a more sustainable future;
Become an expert in e-mobility;
Work in an open and diverse culture with colleagues from all over the world;
Receive a competitive salary that fits your experience + yearly bonus;
Receive a work from home budget to professionally equip your home office
Have XXX paid days of annual leave based on a XXX hour work week
Be able to spend up to 5 working days a year on volunteering
Develop your skills and expertise through several training sessions. Besides this, you will receive a personal training budget and set your annual goals with your personal development plan;
Enjoy our fun get-togethers (drinks), our annual winter and summer outing, and lots of other events or sport teams initiated by colleagues.

Please note: If you don't see yourself fully reflected in every job requirement listed on the posting above, we still encourage you to reach out and apply. Research has shown that women and underrepresented groups often only apply when they feel 100% qualified. We are committed to creating a more equitable, inclusive and diverse company and we strongly encourage applicants of all genders, ages, ethnicities, cultures, abilities, sexual orientation, and life experiences to apply.

Are you looking for an internship in the fast growing e-mobility domain as a product manager? To support the team on product management for strategic initiatives, provide ad-hoc analysis and work closely with our rockstar product and development teams? Interested in working in a fun, fast growing international company with big ambitions?
WE ARE SHELL RECHARGE SOLUTIONS
At Shell Recharge Solutions we are on a mission to enable everybody to drive as many miles as possible powered by clean electricity. We do this by designing, building, and supporting smart charging solutions for business charging, home charging and charging on-the-go. Our award-winning services include charge points, a mobile app and charge cards, that provide access to > 200.000 charge points in over 35 countries - the largest charging network of Europe.

WHAT YOU’LL BE IN CHARGE OF
Understand the CPMS product strategy and roadmap across key internal functional areas, including product development, marketing, sales, operations, finance, and legal, and support go to market activities;
Searching for creative and innovative ideas for product communication and stakeholder information management;
Develop marketing materials for distribution to internal stakeholders for cross-functional enablement;
Support Weekly KPI meetings;
Support the team in documenting and collecting information about our internal initiatives;
Document business requirements in the form of epics and user stories;
Monitor actionable product delivery metrics;
Prepare reports summarising information while making recommendations based on analysis;
Assisting with product roadmap development and prioritisation;
Collaborating with cross-functional teams to ensure product features are delivered on time and within budget;
Assisting with product launches and go-to-market strategies.
THIS IS WHO YOU ARE
You are in your final year of your HBO or WO education. Preferably in (Technical) Business Administration, (Technical) Computer Science, Business Information Management or another technical study;
Strong written and verbal communication skills;
Detail-oriented with the ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously;
Familiarity with agile development methodologies;
Experience with product management tools, such as JIRA or Trello, is a plus;
A passion for technology and innovation, and an eagerness to learn and grow in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.
